Robert M. Pachak, of South Carolina Office of Appellate 
  Defense, of Columbia, for petitioner.
Attorney General Henry Dargan McMaster, Chief Deputy 
  Attorney General John W. McIntosh, Assistant Deputy Attorney General B. Allen 
  Bullard, and Assistant Attorney General David Spencer, all of Columbia, for 
  respondent.
      
    
  


 PER CURIAM:Â  After careful consideration, we dismiss the writ 
  as improvidently granted.Â  See Wolfe v. State, 326 S.C. 158, 485 
  S.E.2d 367 (1997) (defendant who pleads guilty on advice of counsel must show 
  counsel was ineffective).
 TOAL, C.J., MOORE, WALLER, BURNETT and PLEICONES, JJ., concur.





